The script ran successfully. `conclusion.txt` has been written with:

- **Response score: 72** (moderate-to-strong)
- **Key findings**: Mean fishing rate is ~1.1 fish/hour. Hours has a nonlinear effect (strongest predictor at 53.9% importance in SmartAdditive), but the relationship is complex — very short and very long trips yield lower rates, peaking around 0.23–4.7 hours. Group size (persons) is the 2nd strongest predictor (positive effect), while children in the group significantly reduce the rate. Livebait surprisingly shows no independent effect after controlling for other variables.
